    <briefdescription>
<para>Note that we do not store the actual source IP address in the context because the address is already set in the network interface struct. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>If there is no such source address there, the packet cannot be sent anyway. This saves 12 bytes / context in IPv6. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
